snippet.textDisplay:
This is my whole problem with Ryzen 3000. Most people are complaining that even after the bios updates they still are not reaching advertised boost clocks, and if they do, its for a short period. 
I play Blizzard games, WoW and SC2, AMD are not doing so well in those games. Intel shines with them, call it a Blizzard problem, Windows scheduling...whatever, they just don't perform as good as Intel. I am not an Intel shill, I do have a AMD 1600X on a B350 Tomohawk, and while it does ok, fps is all over the place in those games. I am still on a 6700k build that runs much smoother than the 1600X. I am glad AMD is catching up, but they still aren't there 100%. So if you play Blizzard games, even if you play other games, Intel is still the way to go at this moment. At least until Windows and devs start optimizing for Ryzen. 


Me? I am not sold on Zen 2. Especially since the B350 I have, is on beta bios for Zen 2 and unstable from what I have read as others state sometimes the chip isn't even recognized.


Oh and Anthony needs his own show!
